history.content:
Hello! 

My name is Francis Geng, and I am an undergraduate tutor for EECS 16A. If you are an ASE/uGSI in the UAW 2865 (the union for over 19,000 UC academic student employees), you are eligible to vote in the ongoing triannual General Election!

I strongly encourage you all to come out and vote because this will help decide the campus leadership group that will help us all bargain for better contracts and pay!

The voting process is very simple, you don't need to enter any personal information, and it should take less than a minute! The deadline to vote is April 20th, 2021, at 23:59 PM (Today!)

For more information about Head Steward candidates: https://unionforall.org/campus-leadership-berkeley

Steps to vote:

1. Search for "UAW 2865 April 2021 General Election" in your email inbox, the email was sent on April 19. 

2. Click on the direct link in the email or copy and paste your username and passcode to enter the voting portal.

3. Vote for at most 10 candidates!
history.subject: [UAW 2865] Last Day to Vote in General Election!
